title: Google\Cloud\GkeMultiCloud\V1\AwsNodeConfig
name: AwsNodeConfig
description:
Parameters that describe the nodes in a cluster.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.gkemulticloud.v1.AwsNodeConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.instance_type
params.description: Optional. The AWS instance type. When unspecified, it uses a default based on the node pool's version.

params.name: data.root_volume
params.description: Optional. Template for the root volume provisioned for node pool nodes. Volumes will be provisioned in the availability zone assigned to the node pool subnet. When unspecified, it defaults to 32 GiB with the GP2 volume type.

params.name: data.taints
params.description: Optional. The initial taints assigned to nodes of this node pool.

params.name: data.labels
params.description: Optional. The initial labels assigned to nodes of this node pool. An object containing a list of "key": value pairs. Example: { "name": "wrench", "mass": "1.3kg", "count": "3" }.

params.name: data.tags
params.description: Optional. Key/value metadata to assign to each underlying AWS resource. Specify at most 50 pairs containing alphanumerics, spaces, and symbols (.+-=_:@/). Keys can be up to 127 Unicode characters. Values can be up to 255 Unicode characters.

params.name: data.iam_instance_profile
params.description: Required. The name or ARN of the AWS IAM role assigned to nodes in the pool.

params.name: data.image_type
params.description: Optional. The OS image type to use on node pool instances. Can have a value of ubuntu, or windows if the cluster enables the Windows node pool preview feature. When unspecified, it defaults to ubuntu.

params.name: data.ssh_config
params.description: Optional. The SSH configuration.

params.name: data.security_group_ids
params.description: Optional. The IDs of additional security groups to add to nodes in this pool. The manager will automatically create security groups with minimum rules needed for a functioning cluster.

params.name: data.proxy_config
params.description: Optional. Proxy configuration for outbound HTTP(S) traffic.

params.name: data.config_encryption
params.description: Required. Config encryption for user data.

params.name: data.instance_placement
params.description: Optional. Placement related info for this node. When unspecified, the VPC's default tenancy will be used.
